  "prompt": "Can you get pregnant without cervical mucus?",
  "response": "Yes, it is still possible to get pregnant without cervical mucus, but it may be more challenging. Cervical mucus plays an important role in fertility, as it helps sperm travel through the cervix to meet an egg. During the ovulation phase of the menstrual cycle, a woman typically produces more fertile cervical mucus, which is clear, stretchy, and resembles egg whites.\n\nIf a woman has little or no cervical mucus\u2014due to factors such as hormonal imbalances, certain medications, dehydration, or health conditions\u2014sperm may have a harder time moving through the cervix to fertilize an egg. However, if sperm are introduced into the vagina during the fertile window (the days leading up to and including ovulation), pregnancy can still occur, although the chances may be lower.\n\nIf you are trying to conceive and are concerned about your cervical mucus, it may be helpful to consult with a healthcare professional for advice and possible treatments to improve fertility.",
